  "text": "Students at wave 0 completed the Mood and Feelings Questionnaire (MFQ), a 33-item self-report scale eliciting information about depressive symptoms occurring in the previous fortnight. The MFQ has been validated as a screening tool for clinical unipolar depression in adolescents [CITATION_1] ; higher summed MFQ scores are indicative of increased risk [CITATION_2] . Students rated their symptoms on a fourpoint scale (never/sometimes/mostly/always) from which a summed score was computed and used in analyses. In the ROOTS study, internal consistency of the separate items of the MFQ has been demonstrated to be high (Cronbach's α = 0.96).",
